Secondary prevention of breast cancer in older women.

Van Hoeyweghen RJ(1).

Author information:
(1)Algemeen Ziekenhuis Sint-Jan A.V. Ruddershove 10 8000 Brugge, Belgium. 
raf-vanhoeyweghen@azbrugge.be

Periodic mammography is well studied and widely applied as a screening programme 
to reduce breast cancer-related mortality and morbidity in women aged 50 to 69 
years. Despite the fact that age is a major risk factor for breast cancer, no 
evidence-based data are available on survival benefit of screening in women 
older than 69 years. The most commonly cited guidelines for screening in breast 
